snippet.textDisplay: This game broke my heart. It started off promising but it fell apart in nearly every area as it went along. The plot twist just further added insult to injury. This series and me in general don't seem to click as even the remake of the original bored me and SO4 was terrible. SO2 is considered the holy grail in the franchise but seeing as I have disliked every other SO game and their design is the same at the core and didn't do anything for me, may be the series for me in general that I can't enjoy.

snippet.textDisplay:
Most fun charater to me is still Cliff on FAM (best feature of the entire game) with Hammer of Might on both X-Long and O-Long. ;-) But of course nothing can stand up to Mario especially in post game dungeons. I managed to get all three "Freya on 4D" Battle Trophies at the same time with only Maria even though I ran out of Stun Bombs halfway through the fight. That's how overpowered she is.
Never used Albel though aside from my very first playthrough.

snippet.textDisplay:
Star Ocean: The Second Story is truly one of my favorite games of all time. This one wasn't quite as good, but still a solid game, and the "twist" for me, at least, was creative. Not necessarily great, but interesting enough. Nothing touches SO2, however, and I know the series has only gotten worse throughout its sequels, unfortunately.

Thanks!

snippet.textDisplay: Honestly I did rly enjoy this game, right up until the near end of the game, where the big 'Twist' happens, or rather moment of ruin as I like to call it. I think it was a huge cop out of a good story. All this build up and fear of this unknown force only to find out it was all nothing. I much prefer any of the other Star Ocean Games, specifically The Second Story, and The Last Hope, but hey that's just me :)

snippet.textDisplay: I really liked this game. I know a lot of people hated the story's big twist, but it personally didn't bother me at all. I loved the gameplay and the soundtrack by Sakuraba had some very solid tracks (Rust Color being a favorite of mine). I usually always choose to control the main character in an RPG (for example, the Tales games), but this is one of the very few where I didn't; I controlled Albel instead, he was pretty overpowered.
